01:01.961 --> 01:03.861
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.230 --> 01:07.199
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:23.983 --> 01:26.952
- [ Alarm Buzzing ]
- Snooze.

01:27.053 --> 01:30.250
Need more snooze.
[ Muttering ]

01:46.806 --> 01:49.138
[ Yawns ]
Mmm.

01:49.242 --> 01:51.142
- [ Buzzing ]
- [ Screams ]

01:51.244 --> 01:54.213
Num-num, Maggie! Num-num!

01:54.314 --> 01:57.010
Did somebody say, "Num-num"?.

01:57.117 --> 02:00.416
[ Groans ] I can't get Maggie to eat.
May be if you try.

02:00.520 --> 02:04.149
Oh, I'm 26 hours late for work.
No time for Maggie.

02:04.257 --> 02:07.055
Ooh! Where's Waldo?. Nope. Nope.

02:07.160 --> 02:09.924
This would be a lot easier
without all these people. Nope.

02:10.029 --> 02:11.929
Nope. He's there! Uh, no.

02:12.031 --> 02:15.364
- Homer!
- Waldo, where are you?.

02:16.402 --> 02:18.302
[ Whines ]

02:18.404 --> 02:20.099
[Door Closes]

02:20.206 --> 02:22.834
- [Horns Honking]
- [ On Radio ] It is a nightmare
out there on the freeways today...

02:22.942 --> 02:26.776
With surface streets jammed and the sidewalks
filled With pushy New Yorkers.

02:26.880 --> 02:28.780
- Hey, man!
- Hey!

02:28.882 --> 02:31.578
How'd you I i ke a Details magazine
up the wazoo?.

02:31.684 --> 02:34.710
[ Grunts ]

02:37.423 --> 02:39.414
[ Siren Wailing ]

02:39.526 --> 02:41.187
Oh, sure. Single me out.

02:41.294 --> 02:44.661
All right, smart guy.
Where's the fire?.

02:44.764 --> 02:47.289
- Over there.
- [Alarm Blaring]

02:49.135 --> 02:52.036
Okay.
You just bought yourself a 3-17:

02:52.138 --> 02:54.333
pointing out police stupidity.

02:54.440 --> 02:58.570
Or is that a 3-14 ?.
Nah, nah. 3-14  is a dog, uh-

02:58.678 --> 03:01.545
No. Or is that a 3-15?.
You're in trouble, pal!

03:01.648 --> 03:03.343
[Bird Cawing]

03:03.449 --> 03:05.940
[ Panting, Chuckling ]

03:06.052 --> 03:09.681
I'd hate to see the look on old Burnsie's face
if he knew I was just gettin' in.

03:09.789 --> 03:11.757
- [ Giggling ]
- [ Clears Throat ]

03:14.594 --> 03:16.562
Hmm. Who is that?

03:16.663 --> 03:18.893
Big ugly nose.

03:18.998 --> 03:22.058
Bald. Liver spot. Liver spot.

03:22.168 --> 03:26.002
- Hmm.
- [ Clearing Throat ]

03:28.041 --> 03:30.874
- [ Cash Register Dings ]
- Turn around, Simpson.

03:30.977 --> 03:33.878
[ Screams ] No! I can't get in trouble
if l can't see you!

03:33.980 --> 03:36.448
I'm afraid he's got us, sir.

03:36.549 --> 03:38.449
[ Screams ]

03:38.551 --> 03:41.987
[Whimpering, Panting ]

03:42.088 --> 03:44.283
Ah. Safe in the core. And now-

03:44.390 --> 03:46.824
[ Gagging ]
Oh!

03:46.926 --> 03:49.190
- Don't forget the leg protectors, sir.
- Ah, yes.

03:49.295 --> 03:53.026
[ Grunting ]
Ow! Yii! Oh!

03:53.132 --> 03:56.192
I knew I had those installed
for a reason.

03:56.302 --> 03:59.328
- [ Grunts, Gags ]
- [ Grunting ]

04:04.711 --> 04:06.679
Aw, this is the worst day ever!

04:06.779 --> 04:08.679
Hey, Homer. What gives?.

04:08.781 --> 04:11.773
Mr. Burns is making me eat
all these drums of toxic waste.

04:11.884 --> 04:15.513
Geez. That's rough. There must be
200, 300 gallons in here.

04:15.622 --> 04:18.988
Yeah. And even a teaspoon
could cause a fatal tumor.

04:19.091 --> 04:22.528
- Hey, you wanna come bowling with us tonight?.
- Okay.

04:22.629 --> 04:26.156
[Phone Ringing]

04:26.266 --> 04:28.734
Hello?. Homer?. Where are you?.

04:28.835 --> 04:31.599
You promised you were going
to have a tea party with Maggie.

04:33.973 --> 04:36.237
Oh, Marge, I'm sorry.
I can't make it.

04:36.342 --> 04:39.641
The cooling tank just blew,
and they're taking Lenny to the hospital.

04:39.746 --> 04:41.771
Oh, no! Not Lenny!

04:41.881 --> 04:43.781
Not Lenny!

04:43.883 --> 04:45.851
Yes, I'm going to have to work late...

04:45.952 --> 04:48.648
instead of seeing you and the kids,
which is what I really want.

04:48.755 --> 04:51.223
Okay. Sure.

04:51.324 --> 04:53.451
Kids, turn off the TV.

04:53.559 --> 04:56.892
I have some bad news about Lenny.

04:56.996 --> 04:58.691
[ Both ]
Not Lenny!

04:58.798 --> 05:03.326
[ Laughing ] Hey, Carl!
Check out the overhead scoreboard.

05:03.436 --> 05:05.563
[ Both Laughing]

05:05.672 --> 05:08.800
Poo. Uh, Homer.
What wacky name do you want?.

05:08.908 --> 05:10.876
- Are "Poo" and "Ass" taken?.
- Yeah.

05:10.977 --> 05:13.502
Damn!
Could my life get any worse?.

05:13.613 --> 05:15.581
Simpson!
[ Disgusted Sigh ]

05:15.682 --> 05:17.741
Even for a bowler, you're fat.

05:17.850 --> 05:20.944
Hey, guys. Is it normal to see
Burns's face on a bowling ball?.

05:21.054 --> 05:23.818
Ah, actually, I'd say you're having
a severe psychotic episode.

05:23.923 --> 05:26.983
Oh, what a rotten day!

05:27.093 --> 05:28.993
[ Grunts ]

05:30.396 --> 05:32.296
Wow! A strike!

05:32.398 --> 05:36.027
Hey, if that's psychotic,
then why am I takin' these?.

05:36.135 --> 05:38.603
[ Machinery Rattling ]

05:38.705 --> 05:42.232
Oh! You're polishing bone!

05:44.811 --> 05:46.711
[ Pins Falling]

05:46.813 --> 05:49.077
Hey, Homer.
That's four strikes in a row!

05:49.182 --> 05:51.241
- You got a perfect game going.
- Really?.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.342
Careful what you say, Lenny.
You'll jinx it.

05:53.453 --> 05:56.217
All right. Sorry.

05:56.322 --> 05:59.951
Miss! Miss!
Sorry. I Was callin' the Waitress.

06:00.059 --> 06:02.584
Ah, this split you sold me
is makin' me choke.

06:02.695 --> 06:06.153
- Lenny!
- What?. I paid 7.10 for this split.

06:06.265 --> 06:08.893
Will you at least call it a "banana split,"
you dumb wad?.

06:09.001 --> 06:13.267
Hey, spare me your gutter mouth!
Ow. Ow!

06:22.749 --> 06:25.843
Practice ball. Practice ball.

06:25.952 --> 06:29.115
Real, real, real, real, real!
Whoo-hoo!

06:31.524 --> 06:36.393
Kids, today we have to talk about Krusty brand
Chew Goo Gum-Like Substance.

06:36.496 --> 06:38.464
We knew it contained spider eggs...

06:38.564 --> 06:42.056
but the hantavirus-
well, that really came out of left field.

06:43.903 --> 06:46.929
So if any of you have experienced
numbness or comas...

06:47.039 --> 06:49.439
send proof of purchase
and five dollars to:

06:49.542 --> 06:52.340
Antidote, PO. Box 14-

06:52.445 --> 06:55.243
This is Kent Brockman live
from Barney's Bowlarama...

06:55.348 --> 06:58.875
where local pinhead, Homer Simpson,
is on the verge of a perfect game!

06:58.985 --> 07:01.783
Hey, there was no accident
at the plant.

07:01.888 --> 07:04.083
Dad just wanted to go bowling.

07:04.190 --> 07:06.181
He shouldn't have deceived me...

07:06.292 --> 07:09.659
but I'm just so relieved Lenny's okay.

07:09.762 --> 07:14.426
This could be the greatest individual
achievement in the history of Springfield.

07:14.534 --> 07:17.059
- Which proves just how pitiful this town is.
- [ Groaning ]

07:17.170 --> 07:19.070
[ Disgusted Sigh ]
Morons.

07:19.172 --> 07:21.140
[ Crowd ]
Homer! Homer!

07:21.240 --> 07:23.504
Homer!

07:25.378 --> 07:28.108
- [ All ] Yea!
- Whoo-hoo!

07:28.214 --> 07:31.206
I'm 10 pins away from perfection!

07:32.518 --> 07:35.487
Now, listen, your father
really needs to concentrate...

07:35.588 --> 07:38.648
so we'll just stay here
and not disturb him.

07:38.758 --> 07:41.158
Why won't they come over?.

07:41.260 --> 07:43.160
I'm so lonely.

07:43.262 --> 07:47.096
This is it- the ball that will determine
whether Homer Simpson rolls a perfect game...

07:47.200 --> 07:49.760
or a pathetic 290-something.

07:50.903 --> 07:53.371
[ Cheering ]

07:56.709 --> 08:00.008
- Yea! Yea!
- [ Chuckling ] What's wrong, Abe?.

08:00.112 --> 08:03.104
This is as fast as I can move.

08:15.328 --> 08:17.023
Get down. Get down.

08:23.169 --> 08:26.536
- [ Cheering]
- [Firecracker Whistling]

08:40.653 --> 08:43.844
Whoo-hoo!
This is the greatest day of my life!

08:49.595 --> 08:51.085
[ Crowd Cheering ]

08:51.197 --> 08:53.859
[ Kisses ]
You did it, Homie.

08:55.101 --> 08:57.126
In your face, to-do list!

08:57.236 --> 09:00.296
- Homer! Homer!
- Thankyou. Thankyou.

09:00.406 --> 09:03.102
But there was someone else
with me on that alley.

09:03.209 --> 09:06.645
I'm talkin' about the big man- Carl!

09:06.746 --> 09:09.374
Aw, can the corn, bonehead.

09:12.874 --> 09:15.474
Children Today's local hero is
Homer Simpson

09:15.888 --> 09:17.612
[ All ]
Yea!

09:17.623 --> 09:19.889
Mr. Simpson bowled a perfect game...

09:20.293 --> 09:22.921
without the aid of steroids,
crack, angel dust...

09:23.029 --> 09:26.829
or the other narcotics that are
synonymous with pro bowling.

09:26.933 --> 09:29.367
Thank you, Bart's teacher.

09:30.970 --> 09:34.633
You know, kids, my teachers said
I would never amount to anything...

09:34.740 --> 09:37.208
and until last week
they were dead right.

09:37.310 --> 09:40.177
But now I've achieved perfection.

09:43.049 --> 09:45.347
Hmm.

09:45.451 --> 09:48.045
Any questions?.
Yes. Bart's weird friend.

09:48.154 --> 09:50.782
- Will you be my dad?.
- [ Chuckling ]

09:50.890 --> 09:53.620
You've got a father.
He's just a dud. Next question.

09:53.726 --> 09:56.889
- Yes. The girl Bart has a crush on.
- [ Groans ]

09:56.996 --> 09:59.157
Do you think I could grow up
to be a doctor?.

09:59.265 --> 10:01.563
Hey, this was supposed
to be about me.

10:01.667 --> 10:03.828
Now, any other questions?.
Pumpkin face?.

10:03.936 --> 10:06.200
Headgear? Chicken pox?

10:06.305 --> 10:08.603
Smelly? Lazy eye? Spikyhead?

10:10.076 --> 10:12.840
Okay. Class dismissed. Rock on!

10:12.945 --> 10:16.472
- Hooray!
- Wanna split the birthday cupcakes?.

10:16.582 --> 10:19.847
[ Man Announcing] Live frrom Shelbbyville,
it's The Springfield Squares...

10:19.952 --> 10:23.820
featuring our new center square,
Homer "Perfect Game"Simpson.

10:23.923 --> 10:26.050
[ Cheering ]

10:26.158 --> 10:28.217
Hey! Hi, Ron.
[ Grunting ]

10:28.327 --> 10:30.818
[ Groans ]
There's a stairway, dumb-ass!

10:30.930 --> 10:34.889
[ Laughing ] Okay. We'll start with
our returning champion, Disco Stu!

10:35.001 --> 10:39.301
Disco Stu's gonna groove up some dough
playing tic-tac-toe.

10:39.405 --> 10:42.533
Stu, we like to downplay
the resemblance to tic-tac-toe.

10:42.642 --> 10:45.304
I can dig it.
Hit me with the center square.

10:45.411 --> 10:48.175
- [Kent Brockman ] Uh, Homer?
- Yes, Kent?.

10:48.280 --> 10:52.011
According to Redbook magazine,
what is the speed of light?.

10:52.118 --> 10:54.712
Well, that- Uh, well, wait.

10:54.820 --> 10:57.516
Uh, do I read from the sheet
labeled "jokes" or "answers"?.

10:57.623 --> 10:59.488
Oh, for the lo- Stop tape!

10:59.592 --> 11:02.459
Make me center square, Kent.
I'm ready. I can handle it.

11:02.561 --> 11:05.997
- Dream on, drunkie.
- Oh, that's it! You're goin' down!

11:06.098 --> 11:08.658
- [ Grunting ]
- [ Gasping, Screams ]

11:08.768 --> 11:11.703
Stop it, you two!
You're making Scratchy cry!

11:11.804 --> 11:14.432
Oh, we've got to stop putting
these flavors of the month on.

11:14.540 --> 11:16.565
Flavor ofthe month?. Me?.

11:16.676 --> 11:20.134
Yeah, Homer. You can't just ride
one accomplishment forever.

11:20.246 --> 11:23.238
Why do you think I stopped acting
and became a director?.

11:23.349 --> 11:25.613
I don't know.
'Cause you weren't cute anymore?.

11:25.718 --> 11:29.176
- Mmm. I'll agree.
- Circle gets the square. Good night, everyone!

11:29.288 --> 11:30.778
[ Grunts ]

11:34.493 --> 11:38.862
Now, before my partner Teller
hits the shark-infested water...

11:38.964 --> 11:40.932
I'll need to borrow someone's crossbow.

11:41.033 --> 11:43.331
- Here! Here!
- I only need one.

11:46.706 --> 11:49.300
Now, to save my partner's life,
I'll need complete-

11:49.408 --> 11:54.277
Hello, everybody!
Did somebody say "A perfect game"?

11:54.380 --> 11:56.610
You idiot!
You'll ruin everything!

11:56.716 --> 11:59.549
I'm doing a walk-on.
It's a show business thing.

11:59.652 --> 12:01.847
So, how you all doing?. Let's see.

12:01.954 --> 12:03.922
What's in the news today?.

12:04.023 --> 12:06.821
- Will you shut up?.
- Hey, I thought you never talked.

12:06.926 --> 12:10.293
Uh, I didn't mean to.
Huh. It just slipped out.

12:10.396 --> 12:13.024
Oh, God!
Now Penn's gonna beat me.

12:13.132 --> 12:15.362
[ Laughs ]
Folks, it's all part of the act.

12:15.468 --> 12:17.834
No, it isn't.
Don't leave me alone with him!

12:17.937 --> 12:19.928
You've ruined the act!
I'm gonna kill you!

12:20.039 --> 12:22.007
He'll do it.
I'm not the first Teller.

12:22.108 --> 12:25.635
- Remember, Springfield: Keep on swingin'!
- Hey, come here!

12:25.745 --> 12:28.771
I-I just wanna talk to you!
Come here! Come here!

12:28.881 --> 12:30.371
Ooh. Ooh. Guys?.

12:32.118 --> 12:35.679
Remember, in the whole world,
there's nobody like you.

12:35.788 --> 12:37.688
You're special.

12:38.758 --> 12:41.090
So special.

12:41.193 --> 12:44.219
That's right! You are.
[ Giggling ]

12:44.330 --> 12:47.026
Hey, everybody!
I'm gonna be on TV again.

12:47.133 --> 12:49.033
[ Band ]

12:49.135 --> 12:51.160
[ Whines ]

12:51.270 --> 12:55.229
That's right.
You've got a special daddy.

12:55.341 --> 12:58.833
Burt Reynolds apologized to the pope
and promised to replace the windshield.

12:58.944 --> 13:00.844
Burt Reynolds- class act.

13:00.946 --> 13:05.110
Well, now for our weekly segment,
"Yesterday's News," featuring Homer Simpson.

13:05.217 --> 13:08.880
Are you as bored as I am with the antics
of this warmed-over Fred Flintstone?.

13:08.988 --> 13:12.549
I say it's time to put this
one-trick pony out to stud.

13:12.658 --> 13:14.956
Whoo-hoo!
First up, Maude Flanders.

13:15.060 --> 13:17.028
- Homer!
- But she said I-

13:17.129 --> 13:19.893
Dad, what she's saying is you've
had your moment in the sun...

13:19.999 --> 13:23.230
and now it's time for you
to gracefully step aside.

13:23.335 --> 13:25.701
Lisa, I know what's going on here.

13:25.805 --> 13:28.865
They did it to Jesus,
and now they're doing it to me.

13:28.974 --> 13:31.442
Are you comparing yourself
to our Lord?.

13:30.849 --> 13:33.449
Well in bowling ability

13:35.649 --> 13:37.149
Sweet Bowling alley Balloon

13:38.050 --> 13:39.677
you're my only friend.

13:39.785 --> 13:43.346
[ Inhales, Gagging, Coughing ]

13:43.455 --> 13:46.015
[ Grunts ]
What was that about?.

13:46.125 --> 13:48.093
Marge, has my life peaked?.

13:48.194 --> 13:51.561
Oh, Homie.
Is that what's bothering you?.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.564
Mm-hmm.

13:53.666 --> 13:57.659
Well, the one sure cure for the blues
is to talk it over with your life partner.

13:57.770 --> 13:59.670
You're right!

13:59.772 --> 14:01.672
I can't believe it, Moe.

14:01.672 --> 14:04.146
The greatest feet of my life is
already forgotten

14:04.146 --> 14:05.546
Geez Homer

14:05.646 --> 14:06.946
I never seen you this depressed

14:07.047 --> 14:09.379
As your life partner, I'm very worried.

14:09.782 --> 14:11.977
Save your tears, Moe.

14:12.084 --> 14:16.453
Save 'em in a shot glass for someone
who still has a shred of hope.

14:16.555 --> 14:19.854
A shred of what?. Sorry.
I was counting the cocktail radishes.

14:19.959 --> 14:22.189
- [ Sighs ]
- Now, where was I?.

14:22.294 --> 14:24.922
Uh, two, three- three radishes.

14:25.030 --> 14:26.930
Three big radishes.

14:29.034 --> 14:31.662
[ Man ]
This is the end

14:31.770 --> 14:35.069
Beautiful friend

14:38.377 --> 14:41.175
[ Singing Along ]
This is the end

14:41.280 --> 14:45.944
My only friend the end

14:46.051 --> 14:51.011
[ Singing Alone ]
Weird scenes inside the gold mine

14:54.426 --> 14:56.326
[ Bell Dings ]

15:00.165 --> 15:01.723
[ Sighs ]

15:03.669 --> 15:05.933
Well, world, this is it.

15:06.038 --> 15:08.905
You know, I always thought
you'd die before me.

15:09.008 --> 15:12.876
Now, as I prepare my soul
for an eternity of fire and poking-

15:12.978 --> 15:15.378
- Yeah, less chat, more splat, pal!
- [ Gasps ]

15:15.481 --> 15:17.608
[ Screams ]

15:19.718 --> 15:23.017
[ Screaming ]

15:23.122 --> 15:25.886
Hey, Mr. S.,
I didn't know you bungeed.

15:25.991 --> 15:29.222
- I want to live!
- No, no! You're too heavy!

15:29.328 --> 15:31.387
It's a glandular problem!

15:31.497 --> 15:35.194
[ Both Screaming ]

15:35.301 --> 15:36.996
Ooh! Morlocks.

15:37.102 --> 15:39.468
C.H.U.D.'s. Mole people!

15:39.571 --> 15:43.940
There is no escape
from the fortress of the moles!

15:44.043 --> 15:46.170
Oh, except that.

15:46.278 --> 15:48.712
Ow!

15:50.015 --> 15:52.279
O Lord, you saved me.

15:52.384 --> 15:55.751
I guess you had some higher purpose
in mind.

15:55.854 --> 15:58.618
Hey! Look out! Oh, dumb-ass.

15:58.724 --> 16:01.249
- You trying to get yourself killed?.
- Not anymore, Ron.

16:01.360 --> 16:04.158
Now I'm looking for something
to dedicate my life to.

16:04.263 --> 16:06.163
Something noble, but easy.

16:06.265 --> 16:08.392
Daddy, stop talking to that bum.

16:08.500 --> 16:12.197
Look, I'd love to help you out, Homer,
but I'm taking my kids to the zoo.

16:12.304 --> 16:16.502
That's great. Even big stars
take their kids to the zoo.

16:16.608 --> 16:20.408
Well, it's a different zoo containing
animals you've never heard of.

16:20.512 --> 16:23.208
Daddy, we're missing
the Fantastapotamus.

16:23.315 --> 16:25.476
She only sings twice a day.

16:25.584 --> 16:28.451
That's it! Kids are the answer.

16:28.554 --> 16:31.546
I'll dedicate my life to my children.

16:31.657 --> 16:34.023
Really?. You have children?.

16:34.126 --> 16:36.094
Oh, well, look.
Here's some money.

16:36.195 --> 16:40.154
No. I don't want
your pity or your money.

16:40.265 --> 16:43.428
Usually when you say that,
you give the money back.

16:43.535 --> 16:45.435
- I do what now?.
- Yoink!

16:45.537 --> 16:47.732
Listen, boy.

16:47.840 --> 16:50.832
I was wondering if you could use
a little more fatherly attention.

16:50.943 --> 16:55.004
No need, Dad. Over the years, I've learned
to find father figures wherever I can.

16:55.114 --> 16:58.140
Construction workers,
the Internet and Nelson here.

16:58.550 --> 17:01.480
If you tie a string around your
finger real tight,

17:01.725 --> 17:03.025
you can make it turn purple.

17:03.625 --> 17:05.125
I can see i am not needed here.

17:07.326 --> 17:09.692
Lisa, honey. Do you need any help
with your homework?.

17:09.994 --> 17:14.432
Sure! You can help me find
three words where "Y" is the vowel.

17:17.903 --> 17:19.803
I've been so blind.

17:19.905 --> 17:23.340
I'll lavish my attention on Maggie,
the forgotten Simpson.

17:23.442 --> 17:26.638
Maggie! It's me, Daddy!

17:26.744 --> 17:29.270
Daddy's gonna spend
a lot more time with you.

17:29.381 --> 17:31.975
Yes, he is. Yes, he is!

17:32.084 --> 17:35.451
[ Babbling ]

17:36.789 --> 17:38.814
[Babbling Continues ]

17:38.924 --> 17:42.223
Where's Maggie?. Where's Maggie?.

17:42.327 --> 17:44.227
Hey, where is she?.

17:44.329 --> 17:46.297
There you are.

17:47.599 --> 17:51.501
Hi, Maggie.
I'm Homie-Womie, the Teletubbie.

17:51.603 --> 17:53.662
And I'm all man,
in case you heard otherwise.

17:53.772 --> 17:57.572
Let's see what's on tummy-vision.

17:57.676 --> 18:01.203
Ow! Oh, that hurts! Ow! Ow!

18:01.313 --> 18:04.282
[Homer]
Whee! Whee!

18:04.383 --> 18:06.874
Don't be scared, Maggie.
Daddy won't drop you.

18:18.964 --> 18:21.728
You're a tough cookie, Maggie,
but I'm gonna win you over...

18:21.834 --> 18:24.268
just like I did with Lisa.

18:24.369 --> 18:27.167
Hi, honey!

18:29.274 --> 18:33.768
Okay, Dads. This is where
your child's trust in you really pays off.

18:33.879 --> 18:35.278
- D'oh!
- [ Whistle Blows ]

18:35.380 --> 18:37.348
Come on! Come on!

18:37.449 --> 18:39.917
Come on, Maggie. You can trust me.

18:40.018 --> 18:42.919
[ Muffled Voice ]
Come to Daddy! Come to Daddy.

18:43.956 --> 18:46.481
Come to Daddy!

18:46.592 --> 18:47.490
[ Sighs ]

18:47.593 --> 18:49.493
I'm sorry, Maggie.

18:49.595 --> 18:52.063
I never realized things between us
had gotten this bad.

18:56.068 --> 18:58.298
What are you pointing at?.

18:58.403 --> 19:00.701
The ocean?.

19:00.806 --> 19:03.832
That's a great idea!
We'll swim in the ocean.

19:06.578 --> 19:09.877
See, Maggie?.
The ocean is just like a bathtub.

19:09.982 --> 19:11.950
Except instead of rubber duckies...

19:12.050 --> 19:14.541
it has barracudas and moray eels.

19:14.653 --> 19:16.553
[ Chuckles ]

19:16.655 --> 19:19.249
[ Screams ]

19:19.358 --> 19:22.054
Nothin' to worry about.
Just a little wave.

19:22.161 --> 19:25.961
And this riptide is certainly nothing
Daddy can't struggle against.

19:26.064 --> 19:28.430
Help! Help! Somebody, help!

19:28.534 --> 19:31.503
[ Gurgles ]
Current... too strong.

19:31.603 --> 19:35.300
I know. If l sink to the bottom,
I can run to the shore.

19:35.407 --> 19:37.375
[ Inhales ]

19:45.217 --> 19:48.015
[ Gasping ]
Maggie, call Aquaman!

19:51.323 --> 19:53.553
[ Grunting ]

20:08.807 --> 20:11.935
[ Gasps, Coughing ]

20:13.278 --> 20:16.805
Maggie, you're swimming!
You swam out to save me!

20:20.018 --> 20:23.044
Oh, you do love me!

20:27.626 --> 20:30.094
Mr. Simpson,
you're going to be fine...

20:30.195 --> 20:33.164
although you do seem to have
swallowed a number of shark eggs.

20:33.265 --> 20:36.132
Actually, that was befrore
I went in the ocean.

20:36.235 --> 20:39.261
- I don't want to pry into your personal life-
- Then don't!

20:39.371 --> 20:43.068
Doctor, how could a little baby save
a full-grown man from drowning?.

20:43.175 --> 20:45.439
[ Laughing ]
It's quite simple.

20:45.544 --> 20:49.708
When a parent's life is in danger,
a child can summon superhuman strength.

20:49.815 --> 20:53.342
Well, all I care about
is that my little girl loves me.

20:53.452 --> 20:57.889
Oh! And we're gonna spend a lot
more time together from now on.

20:57.990 --> 20:59.548
[Bowling Ball Hitting Pins ]

21:09.735 --> 21:13.432
Good girl, Maggie!
You knocked down all the pins.

21:13.538 --> 21:16.063
But you stepped over the line
just a little bit...

21:16.174 --> 21:18.142
so I'll have to give you a five.

21:18.243 --> 21:22.703
And that gives you
a final score of... 295.

21:22.814 --> 21:27.217
Looks like Daddy won.
But 295 is awfully good for a baby.

21:28.587 --> 21:30.487
Yes, it is. It's very good.

21:30.589 --> 21:34.150
And you're a good little baby.
Yes, you are!

21:34.259 --> 21:36.960
[ Giggling ]

21:38.599 --> 21:40.364
[ Maggie Coos ]

22:25.744 --> 22:27.712
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

